	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 3rd 2:00 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't really think you understand how mana is calculated...<br>Basically, don't even question whether you need to get to 200 WIS/INT...you do...just do it and don't ask questions..the mana pts you get per WIS/INT pt before 200 is just insane...get 200 in these areas<br>After 200 however, before lvl 60, each WIS/INT pt is worth 5 mana pts...at lvl 60, its worth 6...<br>Altho, as a lvl 58 druid, I've noticed that before lvl 60 I seem to be getting 6 mana pts per...<br>If you're over 200 with the helm, say it takes you to 203, then yeah, that's definantly going to be good, cuz it gets you past 200<br>But...before 60, 5 WIS and 25 mana are the SAME THING<br>What's 5 X 5???&nbsp;&nbsp;Yeah my pt exactly...<br>In this situation, go for more AC or other stats...if your Mana item also has hp, go there...mix and match, do whatever you want...but if you're going over 200, 25 mana and 5 pts over 200 until lvl 60 are the same thing<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
