	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 24th 12:42 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have to agree with Wilil.&nbsp;&nbsp;I play a middle of the road Shammy, and there are better gear over all that is obtainable at the levels to do these quests.  If you have your character set-up on this site to do a search, you'll see that.  Don't get me wrong, a lot of the Totemic is good gear, and it's not hard to find a lot of the pieces for this epic type quest.....just a pain to get it.  Point....if you like to keep your AC and your mana up because you like your Shammy to be all thing to all situations, doing the entire Totemic quest is a waste of time.  The Helm, Boots(because of the AC and Str.; and it's easy to obtain), Vambraces (because again, it's easy to obtain, and for AC and Agi....got to dodge those hits you know) are probably the only things worth getting.  If you haven't notice too....you don't see to many Shammy wearing the full suit....hint..hint.  The best thing in being a shammy is, that we can do many things well...not great, but we can tank as well as cast, and focusing on one thing like AC is fine, but this limits us from our casting abilities, especially if we can never be as good as a tank.  So my suggestion is, check out all the pieces of gear that is avalible for your shammy, and make a balanced decision on what gear you would like to have.  I've done this whole epic quest and I ended up only keeping four pieces of gear.  I can't say it was a waste of time because I made more pp than I invested in (money spent on Dufrenite).  But on the other hand, I guess it could be said I could have spent the time to obtaining the peices of gear that I didn't keep.  Also keep in mind...and this might just be me....but I feel we shammy have a little more slack in getting gear than a lot of other classes, so you may want to hold onto that plat for something better or spend that plat on making Sow potions to make more money to get something that is better for your shammy and your situation.  Just some thought from shammy to another.....Happy Hunts.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
