	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jul 18th 3:06 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, so here is my experience, and some advice on camping the Glacier Bear.<br>I entered the caves and hung out in the room with the broken teleporter, logged on the whole time, until I saw the first spawn(the 2 wandering IBS's).&nbsp;&nbsp;This is important to do, even if it's camped, because then you will know the spawn schedule.  The schedule *is* 6 hours 45min.  Exactly.  <br>I killed the 2 PH's, then logged for 6 hours.  Also, in my opinion, if you really want this thing it is important to check in at *every* spawn time.  'Cause if you miss one then you no longer know the schedule, as you can't predict when the spawn will be knocked off, etc.  <br>I then logged on and made a new pet, and put sense animal up.  You can pretty much bet it is safe to hang out in the TP room, as they always, always come by there in their routing(and the lich doesn't come in there), but if you feel the need to roam, you can check back and forth between Sulon McMoor's room and the Hut with the 3 IBS's.  Not sure, but I am fairly sure the spawn is random somewhere between these two rooms.<br>I repeated this process, getting only the PH's, 4 times.  The 5th time, I got 1 PH, and the bear. He was down by Sulon Mcmoor.(this is important to note because the placeholder is not a *pair* of IBS's, but actually *each* IBS.  Therefore, you have 2 chances every 8 hours to see the bear.)<br>I killed the bear. He went down super easy, like less than 45seconds.  I used the root/DOT method with pet attack.  He dropped the skin :)<br>So, I logged, and logged back on at the next spawn time, just to see what would happen.  Again, 1 IBS and 1 Bear.  This time he was at the IBS hut.  Killed him again, and let another shammy loot.<br>SO, the point I am making is, this is a nasty camp, but it is a lot easier on you if you just take the time and do it well-- check every spawn time, stay in the caves, etc.<br>Good luck to you :)<br>Indrii Indiiri<br>35th Shaman of The Tribunal<br>Brell Serilis<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
