	   <tr><td colspan=2>As with many camps, you can go about this alot differently with much less stress.&nbsp;&nbsp;Being a Barb Shm I occasionally have to make the pilgrimage back to Halas for spells or if I just get a wild hair.  On those occasions I just make up a few IVU potions and check things out.  If its getting past your bedtime, you can go down there, kill the phs, and check again when you relog the next day or whatever.  I have spent a total of 1-2 hours down in the cave over the time I have played my shaman, and I have gotten the bear twice.  This works, of course, only if you are not one of those desparate people who must camp and get something before they do anything else.  Kinda like the crazy maniacs who will spend 18 hours camping a mammoth cloak (hint: go get some exp and loot and just buy the damn thing, Im sure you can get the money for one in under 18 hours of playing time).<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
